# TypeScript Standards
Use strict TypeScript with no `any` types. All functions must have return types. Use `interface` over `type` for object shapes.

## No Console Logs
Remove all console.log statements before committing. Use proper logging libraries instead.

# Code Style
Use 2-space indentation. Use single quotes for strings. Max line length: 100 characters.

## Testing Requirements
All new functions must have unit tests. Minimum 80% code coverage. Use Vitest for all tests.

# Security Rules
Never commit secrets or API keys. Use environment variables for all credentials. Validate all user input before processing.

## Database
Use parameterized queries only. Never write raw SQL strings with user input. Always use transactions for multi-step writes.
